THE GENUS 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FBF1EABBFB18A905" box="[1108,1262,1782,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9770E17FBF1EABBFB18A905" box="[1108,1262,1782,1803]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="689">BELONUCHUS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2094B589D9770E16FC83EB51FB7BA8F8" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="690" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" type="description">
<paragraph id="6831E602D9770E16FC83EB51FB7BA8F8" blockId="10.[806,1421,1820,1903]" lastBlockId="11.[826,1441,1452,1780]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="690" pageId="10" pageNumber="689">
The present phylogenetic separation of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9770E17FC83EB77FC5FA943" box="[806,937,1850,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9770E17FC83EB77FC5FA943" box="[806,937,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="689">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
agreed well with our earlier doubts about the polyphyly of this genus (
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9770E17FBDCEB14FABAA963" author="Li L &amp; Zhou HZ" box="[1145,1356,1881,1903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="689" pagination="2149 - 2177" refId="ref21123" refString="Li L, Zhou HZ. 2010 c. Revision of the Chinese species of the genus Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Philonthina). Journal of Natural History 44: 2149 - 2177." type="journal article" year="2010">Li &amp; Zhou, 2010c</bibRefCitation>
). The genus was divided into two clades (D and K) as shown in 
<figureCitation id="F0B5FA87D9760E16FF6FE986FECDABEC" box="[202,315,1483,1505]" captionStart="Figure 30" captionStartId="36.[806,885,847,866]" captionTargetBox="[808,1417,198,816]" captionTargetId="figure-541@36.[806,1422,196,817]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Figure 30. Bisnius lubricus sp. nov. A, aedeagus, dorsal (parameral side) view; B, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; C, underside of paramere; D, sternite IX of male; E, sternite VIII of male; F, tergite X of male. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442155/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Figure 30</figureCitation>
. Members of Clade D share common characters including protarsi in both sexes dilated, with modified pale setae ventrally and paramere of aedeagus well developed, with peg setae on underside of paramere. This clade is not the real 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FD24EA08FCF2A856" box="[641,772,1605,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FD24EA08FCF2A856" box="[641,772,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FEF7EA29FD30A876" authority="Motschulsky, 1860" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1860" box="[338,710,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Trapeziderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FEF7EA29FE13A875" box="[338,485,1636,1657]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Trapeziderus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9760E16FE55EA29FD30A876" author="Motschulsky V" box="[496,710,1636,1658]" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" pagination="25 - 118" refId="ref21270" refString="Motschulsky V. 1860. Entomologie speciale. Insectes des Indes orientales, et de contrees analogues. Etudes Entomologiques 8: 25 - 118." type="journal article" year="1860">Motschulsky, 1860</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(as a synonym of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FE62EACEFDBCA894" box="[455,586,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FE62EACEFDBCA894" box="[455,586,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the current classification; 
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9760E16FEE2EAECFDE0A8BB" author="Li L &amp; Zhou HZ" box="[327,534,1697,1719]" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" pagination="2149 - 2177" refId="ref21123" refString="Li L, Zhou HZ. 2010 c. Revision of the Chinese species of the genus Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Philonthina). Journal of Natural History 44: 2149 - 2177." type="journal article" year="2010">Li &amp; Zhou, 2010c</bibRefCitation>
). Clade K represents the strict 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FEBBEA8DFE57A8D9" box="[286,417,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FEBBEA8DFE57A8D9" box="[286,417,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
erected by 
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9760E16FD90EA8DFCF0A8DA" author="Nordmann A" box="[565,774,1728,1750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" pagination="1 - 167" refId="ref21549" refString="Nordmann A. 1837. Symbolae ad monographiam staphylinorum. In: Ex academiae caesareae scientiarum, Vol. 4. Petropoli: Academiae Caesareae Scientiarum, 1 - 167." type="book chapter" year="1837">Nordmann (1837)</bibRefCitation>
, with the following shared characters: protarsi simple in both sexes, not dilated, lacking modified pale setae ventrally and paramere of aedeagus usually reduced to very small, without peg setae on underside of paramere. 
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9760E16FE87EB14FE2FA963" author="Smetana A" box="[290,473,1881,1903]" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" pagination="1 - 946" refId="ref21981" refString="Smetana A. 1995. Rove beetles of the subtribe Philonthina of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) classification, phylogeny and taxonomic revision. Memoirs on Entomology, International 3: 1 - 946." type="journal article" year="1995">Smetana (1995)</bibRefCitation>
supported the monophyly of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FC4EE9E1FB98ABCD" box="[1003,1134,1452,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FC4EE9E1FB98ABCD" box="[1003,1134,1452,1473]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only included four Nearctic species in his phylogenetic analysis. All of those belong to the strict 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FBC6E9A7FB10ABF3" box="[1123,1254,1514,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FBC6E9A7FB10ABF3" box="[1123,1254,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
erected by 
<bibRefCitation id="0C1F9BF3D9760E16FACBE9A7FC10A812" author="Nordmann A" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" pagination="1 - 167" refId="ref21549" refString="Nordmann A. 1837. Symbolae ad monographiam staphylinorum. In: Ex academiae caesareae scientiarum, Vol. 4. Petropoli: Academiae Caesareae Scientiarum, 1 - 167." type="book chapter" year="1837">Nordmann (1837)</bibRefCitation>
. The old genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FB64EA45FAB2A811" box="[1217,1348,1544,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FB64EA45FAB2A811" box="[1217,1348,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be taxonomically redefined; the name must be restricted to Clade K taxa (and related ones not included in this study). Clade D is expected to be treated as a separate genus in the future. This problem can be successfully solved once a comprehensive revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF8E9D81D9760E16FBDCEA8DFB0AA8D9" box="[1145,1276,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AFA3A10D9760E16FBDCEA8DFB0AA8D9" box="[1145,1276,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="690">Belonuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the world fauna is accomplished.
</paragraph>
